creator: librivoxbooeks
description: LibriVox recording of Newspaper Articles by Mark Twain, by Mark Twain. Read by John Greenman. This is a collection of newspaper articles written by Samuel Clemens, for various newspapers, between 1862 and 1881. After Feb 3rd 1863, he began using the pen name Mark Twain. This compilation is the work of Project Gutenberg and contains articles from: TERRITORIAL ENTERPRISE 1862-1868 THE SAN FRANCISCO DAILY MORNING CALL-1864 THE SACRAMENTO DAILY UNION-1866 DAILY HAWAIIAN HERALD-1866 ALTA CALIFORNIA 1866-1869 THE CHICAGO REPUBLICAN-1868 THE GALAXY 1870-1871 (Introduction by John Greenman) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
